title: Button, late 19th century
description:
Components -a,-c,-e/-h are on card i80-3
Seven circular brass buttons with shanks. a,c,d: marked: Extra Quality; e/h: marked: Horstmann and Allien N Y; a/d: spread eagle on a shield showing, at left, sun above mountains and, at right, stars and stripes, surrounded by 13 stars and the word: Excelsior; e/h: spread eagle with olive branch and three arrows; on breast, shield with the letter A.
